1
00:00:09,325 --> 00:00:14,050
(This program is intended for mature audiences.
It may feature explicit content, violence, and strong language)

2
00:00:14,050 --> 00:00:20,050
(All characters, places, and events
in this series are entirely fictitious)

3
00:00:26,849 --> 00:00:27,490
Mm.

4
00:00:29,263 --> 00:00:29,989
Hmm.

5
00:00:30,530 --> 00:00:33,755
I'm off to work now.
I'll call you in the evening.

6
00:00:34,211 --> 00:00:36,507
Hmm, so...

7
00:00:39,412 --> 00:00:41,100
If I could give you a ride,

8
00:00:41,100 --> 00:00:43,262
I'd do it every single day.

9
00:00:43,819 --> 00:00:45,896
So we could spend more time together.

10
00:00:49,240 --> 00:00:50,460
Should we...

11
00:00:52,064 --> 00:00:53,242
go public?

12
00:00:56,399 --> 00:00:57,885
I'll talk to my family myself.

13
00:01:02,056 --> 00:01:03,306
Honestly, right now,

14
00:01:04,150 --> 00:01:05,906
I don't really care

15
00:01:06,227 --> 00:01:08,338
whether we go public or not.

16
00:01:10,212 --> 00:01:12,188
As long as you're happy,

17
00:01:13,623 --> 00:01:15,227
that's enough for me.

18
00:01:20,918 --> 00:01:22,961
But we can't go on like this forever.

19
00:01:23,822 --> 00:01:25,612
Someday, I'll have to tell my family.

20
00:01:26,778 --> 00:01:27,993
Yeah.

21
00:01:28,365 --> 00:01:31,269
But I have to go now, or I'll be late.

22
00:01:31,810 --> 00:01:32,924
Okay, come here.

23
00:01:34,072 --> 00:01:35,204
- Your arm.
- Mm.

24
00:01:36,690 --> 00:01:37,585
Hup.

25
00:01:38,294 --> 00:01:39,324
Come here.

26
00:01:43,140 --> 00:01:45,116
Wow, you look handsome.

27
00:01:46,078 --> 00:01:46,906
Go.

28
00:01:48,442 --> 00:01:50,874
Go.

29
00:01:54,437 --> 00:01:57,460
Hey, I got you a little something.
Share it with your friends.

30
00:02:00,567 --> 00:02:01,479
Wait.

31
00:02:07,845 --> 00:02:09,044
Drive safe, okay?

32
00:02:09,415 --> 00:02:10,969
- Sure.
- Bye.

33
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:40,131
=Love of Silom=

34
00:02:45,096 --> 00:02:46,261
Mm.

35
00:02:46,615 --> 00:02:47,612
Hi, everyone.

36
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,115
Hello, Captain.

37
00:02:50,094 --> 00:02:52,829
I got this for you.
Share it around, okay?

38
00:02:52,829 --> 00:02:54,535
Thank you.

39
00:02:55,379 --> 00:02:57,980
- Please handle this soon.
- Got it.

40
00:02:58,655 --> 00:03:01,137
Inspector, this is for you.

41
00:03:03,164 --> 00:03:05,731
Oh, thanks a lot.

42
00:03:06,406 --> 00:03:08,079
(Police Captain, Deputy Investigation Inspector)
Captain.

43
00:03:08,079 --> 00:03:09,749
(Kritsadawut Siriwatmontri)
Someone's here to see you.

44
00:03:09,952 --> 00:03:10,999
Who is it?

45
00:03:25,926 --> 00:03:27,666
Showing up at my office now?

46
00:03:28,729 --> 00:03:31,296
Are you free? I need to talk to you
about something important.

47
00:03:32,867 --> 00:03:36,007
You came all this way, so let's talk.

48
00:03:37,848 --> 00:03:40,026
- Let's talk in my office.
- Mm.

49
00:03:48,689 --> 00:03:51,104
The Captain's girlfriend is stunning.

50
00:03:51,104 --> 00:03:54,294
No wonder he's in such
a good mood today. Haha.

51
00:03:54,294 --> 00:03:59,140
- His world must be all pink right now.
- Wow.

52
00:03:59,868 --> 00:04:02,519
But ours are all black, just work.

53
00:04:02,519 --> 00:04:03,312
Oh.

54
00:04:05,069 --> 00:04:08,496
So what now about the wedding?
I'm not faking a marriage, okay?

55
00:04:08,496 --> 00:04:10,321
Fake dating is already stressful enough.

56
00:04:10,337 --> 00:04:12,921
If I have to fake a wedding too,
I can't do it.

57
00:04:12,921 --> 00:04:15,639
Calm down. Don't overthink it.

58
00:04:16,281 --> 00:04:18,088
Take it one step at a time.
We'll figure something out.

59
00:04:18,189 --> 00:04:22,005
Krit, I'm serious. You can't keep
running away forever.

60
00:04:22,985 --> 00:04:25,602
I know.

61
00:04:26,041 --> 00:04:29,689
Let me close this case first.
Then I'll talk to my parents.

62
00:04:32,424 --> 00:04:37,372
You really need to talk to them,
or we'll end up married.

63
00:04:37,372 --> 00:04:40,310
Your parents already had
a serious talk with mine.

64
00:04:40,310 --> 00:04:42,007
They're already picking a wedding date.

65
00:04:43,349 --> 00:04:45,866
Yeah. I'll take care of it.

66
00:04:46,592 --> 00:04:48,550
For now, can you just go along with it?

67
00:04:48,837 --> 00:04:50,087
Even if you say no,

68
00:04:50,965 --> 00:04:53,279
they'll just find another woman
for me to marry anyway.

69
00:04:55,541 --> 00:04:58,159
Come on, I've helped you
this much already.

70
00:04:59,054 --> 00:05:01,570
Just wrap up the case
and go talk to them.

71
00:05:01,570 --> 00:05:03,005
So we can put an end to this.

72
00:05:06,078 --> 00:05:06,838
Sigh.

73
00:05:35,443 --> 00:05:37,892
Whoa, Wai.

74
00:05:38,128 --> 00:05:39,008
I was only gone for a second.

75
00:05:39,008 --> 00:05:41,024
- What's this, some kind of nightmare factory?
- Dad.

76
00:05:41,024 --> 00:05:42,113
Yes.

77
00:05:42,113 --> 00:05:46,115
Singto, I really miss you.

78
00:05:46,115 --> 00:05:48,479
Give me a cheek kiss quickly, huh.

79
00:05:48,479 --> 00:05:49,678
This is for you.

80
00:05:49,678 --> 00:05:54,152
With you gone, Singto didn't say a word.
This is the first time I hear his voice.

81
00:05:54,152 --> 00:05:56,315
So, did you even try talking to Singto?

82
00:05:56,315 --> 00:05:58,712
Oh, I talked till my mouth went dry.

83
00:05:58,881 --> 00:06:02,022
Wow, you didn't speak at all? It's okay.

84
00:06:02,022 --> 00:06:04,707
It took forever before he would talk
to me too.

85
00:06:05,197 --> 00:06:06,413
Just give him some time.

86
00:06:06,565 --> 00:06:08,118
Oh, Wai!

87
00:06:08,540 --> 00:06:10,600
Hurry up, oh.

88
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,968
Come on, they'll be here
to get it any second.

89
00:06:11,968 --> 00:06:13,116
Okay, got it.

90
00:06:14,552 --> 00:06:17,270
Wai, what are you doing to Mom?

91
00:06:17,507 --> 00:06:20,293
Just keeping her occupied.

92
00:06:20,293 --> 00:06:21,711
You really can't let
your guard down with her.

93
00:06:21,721 --> 00:06:24,176
Next thing you know, she'll be off
gambling or buying lottery tickets.

94
00:06:25,173 --> 00:06:29,091
- Whoa.
- Yeah, I transferred the daycare money.

95
00:06:29,530 --> 00:06:32,299
Hey, why'd you send it? You got money
to spare or what?

96
00:06:32,299 --> 00:06:34,427
Come on. I just wanted to help.

97
00:06:35,102 --> 00:06:37,957
I don't even know what to feel
guilty about first.

98
00:06:37,957 --> 00:06:40,877
The kid, my brother, my mom...

99
00:06:42,768 --> 00:06:44,018
Come on.

100
00:06:44,119 --> 00:06:47,885
Let me do my part as a good sister
and a good mom.

101
00:06:49,270 --> 00:06:52,191
I think you should keep it and use it
to start your business.

102
00:06:52,377 --> 00:06:55,230
I can support my only nephew.

103
00:06:57,426 --> 00:07:00,415
You need to stop carrying
all these problems on your own.

104
00:07:01,022 --> 00:07:03,741
Use that money for yourself for once.

105
00:07:04,045 --> 00:07:05,784
Didn't you put school on hold?

106
00:07:05,784 --> 00:07:07,169
Go back and finish it.

107
00:07:07,540 --> 00:07:10,496
From now on, I will handle
things at home.

108
00:07:10,496 --> 00:07:13,079
And you don't have to worry anymore.

109
00:07:13,180 --> 00:07:14,126
Okay.

110
00:07:16,355 --> 00:07:17,318
Thanks.

111
00:07:19,344 --> 00:07:21,404
Ugh, are you two
going to keep talking forever?

112
00:07:21,404 --> 00:07:24,376
Wai, are you done yet?
They'll be here to pick it up soon.

113
00:07:24,376 --> 00:07:25,879
- Yeah.
- Ugh.

114
00:07:25,879 --> 00:07:27,247
- Jeez.
- Mom.

115
00:07:27,635 --> 00:07:31,147
Hey, are you free? Come help me out.
There are still a bunch of boxes left.

116
00:07:31,147 --> 00:07:33,680
- Aren't you going to say hi first?
- Yeah.

117
00:07:37,041 --> 00:07:38,779
Come on, want to go inside?

118
00:07:38,779 --> 00:07:41,431
Inside? Okay, sure. Let's go.

119
00:07:54,484 --> 00:07:55,345
Oh, Krit.

120
00:07:56,662 --> 00:07:57,625
Is Dad not home?

121
00:07:58,351 --> 00:08:01,610
He went golfing with the minister.
He should be back this evening.

122
00:08:02,252 --> 00:08:03,383
Is something wrong, Krit?

123
00:08:05,105 --> 00:08:06,119
No, Mom. Nothing.

124
00:08:08,702 --> 00:08:11,117
So, was it a tough case?

125
00:08:16,301 --> 00:08:17,348
A little.

126
00:08:18,462 --> 00:08:20,320
Krit, you can tell me anything.

127
00:08:21,671 --> 00:08:23,832
I'll always be here for you, Krit.

128
00:08:24,626 --> 00:08:28,560
And don't push yourself so hard
that you forget to be happy.

129
00:08:42,610 --> 00:08:43,555
Mom.

130
00:08:47,709 --> 00:08:50,985
If I don't turn out the way
you and Dad expected,

131
00:08:52,133 --> 00:08:53,349
will you be disappointed?

132
00:08:57,115 --> 00:08:59,124
Why would you ask that, sweetheart?

133
00:09:02,130 --> 00:09:03,261
I was just wondering.

134
00:09:05,001 --> 00:09:07,162
Well, that depends on what it is.

135
00:09:08,243 --> 00:09:10,117
But I want you to know this, Krit.

136
00:09:10,117 --> 00:09:14,676
I've always been proud of you.

137
00:09:15,487 --> 00:09:18,712
You're a good son and a good officer.

138
00:09:19,151 --> 00:09:22,664
And you're about to marry
someone wonderful like Rose.

139
00:09:24,420 --> 00:09:27,544
I've already prepared
the family ring and jewelry.

140
00:09:28,304 --> 00:09:30,398
They'll suit Rose perfectly.

141
00:09:32,559 --> 00:09:33,505
- Yes.
- Mm.

142
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,345
What is it, Lieutenant?

143
00:09:44,514 --> 00:09:49,276
Captain, we found a body. It may be
a trafficking victim from our case.

144
00:09:49,918 --> 00:09:51,674
Okay, I'll head over right away.

145
00:09:56,267 --> 00:09:57,145
I have to go now, Mom.

146
00:09:58,344 --> 00:10:00,016
Take good care of yourself, okay?

147
00:10:07,413 --> 00:10:11,618
- Wait, an emergency.
- Yes, sir.

148
00:10:30,798 --> 00:10:31,744
Captain.

149
00:10:31,744 --> 00:10:33,214
We received a report that

150
00:10:33,244 --> 00:10:36,628
a body was found in the septic tank
of an abandoned factory.

151
00:10:36,912 --> 00:10:37,790
Here, sir.

152
00:10:39,936 --> 00:10:41,202
The body we found,

153
00:10:41,225 --> 00:10:43,326
all of its internal organs
have been removed.

154
00:10:43,903 --> 00:10:45,912
Only the upper torso is left.

155
00:10:46,216 --> 00:10:48,283
It's enough to identify him,

156
00:10:48,479 --> 00:10:50,691
but the body's in pretty bad shape.

157
00:11:05,028 --> 00:11:05,821
You okay with this?

158
00:11:05,821 --> 00:11:07,611
Of course, this is my level.

159
00:11:07,611 --> 00:11:08,861
You want to learn? I can teach you.

160
00:11:08,861 --> 00:11:10,836
- You can teach me next time.
- Sure, buddy.

161
00:11:10,836 --> 00:11:13,352
- Hey, bro. Hello.
- Hello.

162
00:11:13,352 --> 00:11:15,012
- Wow.
- Hey, Man!

163
00:11:15,012 --> 00:11:15,565
Yes.

164
00:11:15,565 --> 00:11:18,240
- Wow, those muscles are solid.
- Yeah.

165
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,364
Nothing special.

166
00:11:19,364 --> 00:11:20,850
- Tai.
- Hmm?

167
00:11:21,120 --> 00:11:22,505
Do you remember my sister?

168
00:11:24,210 --> 00:11:26,203
Singto's mom, right?

169
00:11:26,828 --> 00:11:27,706
Mm.

170
00:11:28,483 --> 00:11:29,935
She's back home now.

171
00:11:30,087 --> 00:11:31,910
She seems a lot more mature now.

172
00:11:33,194 --> 00:11:35,828
She's selling stuff on livestreams now.
You know that?

173
00:11:36,199 --> 00:11:37,837
She even got my mom in on it.

174
00:11:37,956 --> 00:11:40,202
My mom's so busy now. She doesn't even
have time to play cards.

175
00:11:40,202 --> 00:11:43,157
Whoa, I never thought I'd hear that.

176
00:11:43,157 --> 00:11:45,369
Yeah, me neither.

177
00:11:53,761 --> 00:11:56,497
Do you think I should go back to school?

178
00:11:57,932 --> 00:11:59,300
You think you can handle that?

179
00:11:59,806 --> 00:12:01,765
Working and studying at the same time?

180
00:12:04,180 --> 00:12:06,443
I mean, I do have some savings.

181
00:12:06,443 --> 00:12:10,242
It should cover tuition
and living expenses till I graduate.

182
00:12:11,441 --> 00:12:14,058
Wait, does that mean you're quitting?

183
00:12:16,642 --> 00:12:18,314
Yeah... Something like that.

184
00:12:19,833 --> 00:12:21,708
Are you going back to school, Wayu?

185
00:12:22,434 --> 00:12:24,477
Hey, what were you doing over there?

186
00:12:24,528 --> 00:12:25,744
Yeah, Foei.

187
00:12:28,361 --> 00:12:31,299
I asked if you're going back to school.

188
00:12:32,954 --> 00:12:35,436
Yeah... Something like that.

189
00:12:35,436 --> 00:12:38,222
I still haven't made up
my mind yet, Foei.

190
00:12:38,357 --> 00:12:41,549
If I go back, I only have one year left.

191
00:12:41,566 --> 00:12:43,795
But this is your moment now.

192
00:12:44,774 --> 00:12:45,669
Right now.

193
00:12:46,294 --> 00:12:48,709
You're number one here now.

194
00:12:49,401 --> 00:12:51,377
(Tai, Richy, Wayu, Kenji, Edkie)
I'm not saying anything.

195
00:12:51,799 --> 00:12:53,825
I just want you
to really think it through.

196
00:12:54,011 --> 00:12:55,497
If you go back to school,

197
00:12:55,852 --> 00:12:58,520
can you still keep doing this job?

198
00:13:05,287 --> 00:13:07,844
Are you really going to walk away
from an opportunity like this?

199
00:16:12,863 --> 00:16:15,581
Amazing. Absolutely amazing.

200
00:16:15,581 --> 00:16:18,519
My boys are absolutely slaying!

201
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:20,546
Hmm.

202
00:16:22,640 --> 00:16:25,612
Wayu, the big client chooses you.

203
00:16:26,861 --> 00:16:27,604
Go.

204
00:16:28,178 --> 00:16:28,887
Go on.

205
00:16:30,036 --> 00:16:35,676
Let's hear it for the Moonlit Boys!

206
00:16:36,368 --> 00:16:39,121
If there's anything you need today,
just let me know, Ice.

207
00:16:39,121 --> 00:16:40,522
- Oh.
- I'll take care of it.

208
00:16:40,522 --> 00:16:41,890
Sure. Thank you so much.

209
00:16:43,511 --> 00:16:46,196
Oh, I've eaten already.
Has Mom eaten yet?

210
00:16:46,196 --> 00:16:50,907
- Um? Okay, got it.
- Absolutely cool.

211
00:16:52,954 --> 00:16:53,472
Bangkok.

212
00:17:01,832 --> 00:17:05,716
This is Mr. Ice. He booked you
for 500 drinks. Take good care of him.

213
00:17:05,716 --> 00:17:07,050
Let me hear you louder than that!

214
00:17:09,533 --> 00:17:12,927
If you're ready,
let's have fun to the fullest.

215
00:17:23,413 --> 00:17:24,663
- Hello, Mr. Ice.
- Hello.

216
00:17:24,663 --> 00:17:27,347
- How's your night going?
- Great.

217
00:17:27,347 --> 00:17:29,718
- You're all amazing dancers.
- Oh, thank you.

218
00:17:30,623 --> 00:17:32,886
Hey, could you dance with me for a bit?

219
00:17:32,886 --> 00:17:34,524
Dance? Sure.

220
00:17:34,524 --> 00:17:36,618
So, Mr. Ice, what kind of service
would you like?

221
00:17:36,871 --> 00:17:38,526
Oh, anything is fine.

222
00:17:38,526 --> 00:17:41,616
I'm not much of a dancer.
It's my first time here.

223
00:17:41,785 --> 00:17:43,930
Then try it like this.

224
00:18:02,521 --> 00:18:04,126
Mr. Ice, let me fix you a drink first.

225
00:18:04,126 --> 00:18:05,207
Okay, thanks.

226
00:18:09,664 --> 00:18:14,173
Yeah! Go for it, woo-hoo!

227
00:18:19,002 --> 00:18:21,400
- Go.
- Mr. Ice!

228
00:18:21,788 --> 00:18:23,697
Okay, thanks.

229
00:18:36,750 --> 00:18:38,860
Oh! Hey. Take it easy.

230
00:18:39,283 --> 00:18:40,414
- Easy.
- Fake.

231
00:18:40,414 --> 00:18:42,660
Okay. Slowly.

232
00:18:42,660 --> 00:18:45,412
- Hey, get home safely.
- Yes.

233
00:18:45,412 --> 00:18:47,692
How about three thousand?
Is that enough?

234
00:18:47,692 --> 00:18:50,039
- Sure.
- Just take it.

235
00:18:50,225 --> 00:18:52,100
- Ah. Thank you.
- This way.

236
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:53,247
Hey, come here.

237
00:18:53,737 --> 00:18:55,122
- Two.
- Hello, Mr. Ice.

238
00:18:56,540 --> 00:18:57,384
Oh, really?

239
00:18:57,384 --> 00:18:58,976
- Thank you very much.
- See you.

240
00:18:58,976 --> 00:18:59,951
Careful there.

241
00:18:59,951 --> 00:19:01,235
Hey, Mr. Ice.

242
00:19:01,235 --> 00:19:03,312
- Why are you leaving so early tonight?
- Mm.

243
00:19:03,312 --> 00:19:06,317
You booked me for the whole night,
and now you're leaving this early.

244
00:19:06,486 --> 00:19:09,492
I'm not sure if there's something
you don't like about me.

245
00:19:09,492 --> 00:19:10,944
Or did I do something wrong?

246
00:19:10,944 --> 00:19:14,659
No, not at all.
I had a great time tonight.

247
00:19:14,710 --> 00:19:17,969
- I just can't stay out late.
- Ah.

248
00:19:18,138 --> 00:19:21,194
Well, anyway.

249
00:19:21,481 --> 00:19:24,564
I'll make it up to you next time, okay?

250
00:19:24,564 --> 00:19:26,260
- Sure.
- Okay.

251
00:19:26,277 --> 00:19:29,722
Thanks so much. Just let me know
when you're coming back. Mr. Ice.

252
00:19:29,722 --> 00:19:32,204
- I'll be happy to take care of you.
- Okay.

253
00:19:32,204 --> 00:19:33,859
- See you, bro.
- See you.

254
00:19:33,859 --> 00:19:35,632
Thank you. Whoa!

255
00:19:42,184 --> 00:19:42,994
See you soon.

256
00:19:53,615 --> 00:19:55,118
- This event?
- Yeah.

257
00:19:55,118 --> 00:19:56,283
- This event.
- Pipe.

258
00:19:56,587 --> 00:19:58,411
- Can I get some water?
- Here. This event.

259
00:19:58,411 --> 00:20:00,995
- Hey, take a look.
- You're still going?

260
00:20:01,299 --> 00:20:03,241
- Thanks.
- The cops showed up last time.

261
00:20:04,355 --> 00:20:07,023
There's been a lot of
scary news lately too.

262
00:20:08,357 --> 00:20:10,806
I already said yes. The money's good.

263
00:20:12,393 --> 00:20:14,673
- Yeah.
- Ken.

264
00:20:17,628 --> 00:20:18,675
Where's the party?

265
00:20:19,164 --> 00:20:20,684
Same guy as before, Nut.

266
00:20:20,937 --> 00:20:23,504
He's recruited a bunch of
good-looking host boys.

267
00:20:23,875 --> 00:20:27,472
But it's VIP only. No sharing, no leaks.

268
00:20:36,456 --> 00:20:38,448
Hello, Officer.

269
00:20:38,448 --> 00:20:40,981
You're standing watch here
yourself today?

270
00:20:43,278 --> 00:20:44,071
Krit.

271
00:20:47,229 --> 00:20:50,319
You promised Foei
you wouldn't come here again, right?

272
00:20:50,471 --> 00:20:52,599
Go home, quick. Before Foei sees you.

273
00:20:53,477 --> 00:20:57,817
Oh, come on.

274
00:20:58,188 --> 00:21:02,764
I told you already at the field,
not to come here again.

275
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:08,962
I'm not here to see Wayu.
I'm here for you.

276
00:21:09,721 --> 00:21:10,667
What do you want with me?

277
00:21:12,558 --> 00:21:16,071
I want to ask about Sky.
He works here, right?

278
00:21:17,388 --> 00:21:19,499
"Used to" is the right word.

279
00:21:22,015 --> 00:21:24,024
When was the last time
you were in touch with Sky?

280
00:21:25,290 --> 00:21:27,924
I haven't talked to him.
The bar's been busy lately.

281
00:21:27,924 --> 00:21:29,242
Haven't even had time to call.

282
00:21:30,052 --> 00:21:32,366
Why? Did he get into trouble again?

283
00:21:35,118 --> 00:21:39,289
If you've got something to say, Captain,
just say it. Why are you hesitating?

284
00:21:41,349 --> 00:21:44,608
Not long ago, we got a report that

285
00:21:44,608 --> 00:21:49,049
a body and human organs were found
in the septic tank of an abandoned factory.

286
00:21:51,852 --> 00:21:56,310
We've now confirmed who the victim was.

287
00:21:58,303 --> 00:21:59,384
That body...

288
00:22:02,204 --> 00:22:03,200
was Sky's.

289
00:22:54,787 --> 00:22:56,746
I thought Sky had just gone quiet.

290
00:22:57,827 --> 00:23:00,073
I thought he was off living
a better life in Hong Kong, China.

291
00:23:03,281 --> 00:23:04,311
I never expected.

292
00:23:04,953 --> 00:23:06,337
He'd have to face something like this.

293
00:23:12,467 --> 00:23:13,514
Nobody thinks that.

294
00:23:14,274 --> 00:23:16,705
And no one wants this to happen.

295
00:23:27,057 --> 00:23:27,952
Hey, Krit.

296
00:23:29,336 --> 00:23:33,186
I heard some of the guys at the bar
say Nut's throwing a party.

297
00:23:34,655 --> 00:23:36,209
I already got the details.

298
00:23:37,543 --> 00:23:39,147
Now all that's left is to get inside.

299
00:23:42,068 --> 00:23:43,994
- Let me go in.
- No.

300
00:23:45,834 --> 00:23:49,178
Send me the details.
I'll handle the rest.

301
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:51,896
But I'm already in the VIP group chat.

302
00:23:53,281 --> 00:23:55,003
Getting in shouldn't be that hard.

303
00:23:55,003 --> 00:23:56,540
It's too dangerous.

304
00:23:58,229 --> 00:23:59,765
You saw it yourself, Wayu.

305
00:24:00,621 --> 00:24:02,166
What happened to Sky.

306
00:24:03,109 --> 00:24:04,730
And you still want
to put yourself at risk?

307
00:24:05,101 --> 00:24:08,276
But don't you want to close this case?

308
00:24:09,458 --> 00:24:11,298
If you want to wrap it up fast,

309
00:24:12,075 --> 00:24:13,375
you need me.

310
00:24:18,999 --> 00:24:19,725
Also,

311
00:24:20,468 --> 00:24:21,498
I'm afraid that

312
00:24:22,258 --> 00:24:24,064
this might happen to Tai.

313
00:24:25,770 --> 00:24:26,783
Foei,

314
00:24:27,340 --> 00:24:29,063
or the others at Moonlit.

315
00:24:30,346 --> 00:24:32,372
I don't want this to happen again.

316
00:24:33,318 --> 00:24:34,635
Please let me go in.

317
00:24:38,722 --> 00:24:39,600
Please, Krit.

318
00:24:47,283 --> 00:24:48,009
Okay.

319
00:24:50,694 --> 00:24:51,758
But I'm going in with you.

320
00:24:53,852 --> 00:24:55,675
I can't let you risk it alone.

321
00:25:12,882 --> 00:25:16,260
(Closed for 2 days. Sorry for
the inconvenience.)

322
00:25:17,830 --> 00:25:21,511
(Born January 21, 1998,
Died April 2, 2026)

323
00:25:45,506 --> 00:25:50,960
Though Sky loves stirring up drama,

324
00:25:52,008 --> 00:25:53,865
and he can be a real pain,

325
00:25:54,980 --> 00:25:58,610
(honestly, it's because
he grew up on his own.)

326
00:25:58,610 --> 00:26:00,832
We must win, Team Sky!

327
00:26:00,832 --> 00:26:02,546
- Yay!
- Hey!

328
00:26:03,288 --> 00:26:06,851
(He fights for a better life.)

329
00:26:13,217 --> 00:26:15,125
So don't be mad at him.

330
00:26:16,493 --> 00:26:18,384
He's just trying to survive,
like everyone else.

331
00:26:19,853 --> 00:26:22,420
Thank you so much for helping me.

332
00:26:22,690 --> 00:26:24,902
I didn't expect to hear that from you.

333
00:26:24,902 --> 00:26:26,168
I really am sorry

334
00:26:26,878 --> 00:26:27,776
to both of you.

335
00:26:27,776 --> 00:26:29,394
- Uh-huh.
- I could call to yell at you.

336
00:26:29,394 --> 00:26:30,474
- Haha!
- Come here.

337
00:26:30,474 --> 00:26:32,568
- Ah, come on. Give me a hug.
- Hugs.

338
00:26:32,568 --> 00:26:34,544
Ow.

339
00:26:34,679 --> 00:26:36,368
This kind of terrible thing

340
00:26:38,174 --> 00:26:39,863
should never have happened to him.

341
00:26:41,197 --> 00:26:42,430
Or to anyone else.

342
00:26:50,721 --> 00:26:51,666
I know

343
00:26:53,997 --> 00:26:56,631
you can finally live the life
you always dreamed of.

344
00:27:00,076 --> 00:27:01,258
I just hope heaven

345
00:27:03,993 --> 00:27:07,708
is at least half as fun as Moonlit.

346
00:27:37,512 --> 00:27:39,623
(I'll get the person who did this.)

347
00:27:40,619 --> 00:27:41,565
(I promise.)

348
00:27:42,842 --> 00:27:45,114
(Born January 21, 1998,
Died April 2, 2026)

349
00:28:15,185 --> 00:28:17,296
- You ready?
- Mm.

350
00:28:18,563 --> 00:28:21,788
But this outfit is totally impractical
for the operation.

351
00:28:24,287 --> 00:28:26,161
Don't hosts know how to dress normally?

352
00:28:26,871 --> 00:28:27,749
Hey, Krit,

353
00:28:28,593 --> 00:28:30,602
this theme is pretty basic.

354
00:28:30,805 --> 00:28:32,460
You know we're actually pretty lucky,

355
00:28:32,460 --> 00:28:33,862
since they're letting us wear masks.

356
00:28:48,755 --> 00:28:50,461
Yes, go right ahead.

357
00:28:52,234 --> 00:28:53,466
Go ahead. Thank you.

358
00:28:53,483 --> 00:28:56,371
Please show your face. Go ahead.

359
00:28:56,540 --> 00:28:59,393
Go ahead. Oat, Mos, show your face.

360
00:29:00,322 --> 00:29:01,572
- Wayu.
- Go ahead.

361
00:29:02,011 --> 00:29:03,970
- Wait.
- Is this your friend?

362
00:29:04,442 --> 00:29:06,300
- Yeah.
- Hello.

363
00:29:06,756 --> 00:29:09,035
- Shall we go then?
- Let's go.

364
00:29:13,966 --> 00:29:15,942
- Okay.
- Wayu.

365
00:29:15,942 --> 00:29:17,411
Please go ahead.

366
00:29:19,792 --> 00:29:21,852
- Shall we go first?
- You're the host, right?

367
00:29:22,240 --> 00:29:23,220
We have to move on now.

368
00:29:25,483 --> 00:29:26,513
Oh, host.

369
00:29:26,985 --> 00:29:28,083
Let me check for weapons.

370
00:29:29,131 --> 00:29:30,161
Please go ahead.

371
00:29:31,663 --> 00:29:34,027
You're the host, right?
Show your face too.

372
00:29:40,596 --> 00:29:43,281
Whoa, what happened to you?

373
00:29:45,543 --> 00:29:47,232
This should do it, right?

374
00:29:47,705 --> 00:29:49,039
This stuff stays on, too.

375
00:29:52,348 --> 00:29:56,367
Doesn't this make me look
even more suspicious?

376
00:29:56,570 --> 00:29:59,204
Well, we don't really have a choice.

377
00:29:59,204 --> 00:30:03,510
If Por has a blacklist,
or if he sees you, we're done.

378
00:30:06,786 --> 00:30:10,062
Come on, trust my gift of gab.

379
00:30:10,687 --> 00:30:11,514
Well...

380
00:30:12,612 --> 00:30:14,858
A VIP client asked for this.

381
00:30:15,888 --> 00:30:19,130
No one else is this covered up.
That's kind of weird.

382
00:30:20,785 --> 00:30:23,554
Look, I wasn't supposed to say this,

383
00:30:23,807 --> 00:30:26,340
but he told me to explain
if there was a problem.

384
00:30:28,519 --> 00:30:29,549
Hey...

385
00:30:30,258 --> 00:30:33,787
Por asked for it himself.
He's into this kind of thing.

386
00:30:34,057 --> 00:30:35,560
But he doesn't want anyone to know.

387
00:30:38,448 --> 00:30:39,275
Okay.

388
00:30:39,799 --> 00:30:41,082
Go ahead, go on.

389
00:30:45,709 --> 00:30:47,448
- Nice one.
- Hello.

390
00:30:47,752 --> 00:30:49,170
Now this is the real deal.

391
00:30:59,015 --> 00:31:02,629
Since it's my birthday party,

392
00:31:02,629 --> 00:31:05,955
let's all go wild tonight.

393
00:31:05,955 --> 00:31:11,122
I've got some handsome guys and girls
here to take care of everyone all night.

394
00:31:11,122 --> 00:31:14,736
Whatever kind of service you want,
you can work it out yourselves.

395
00:31:14,736 --> 00:31:16,830
I guarantee

396
00:31:16,830 --> 00:31:20,612
they're top-tier.
You won't be disappointed.

397
00:31:21,136 --> 00:31:27,806
But first, let's kick things off
with an opening show.

398
00:32:06,222 --> 00:32:08,147
Check, one, two, three. Can you hear me?

399
00:32:08,350 --> 00:32:10,494
Wow, it's really clear.

400
00:32:10,849 --> 00:32:13,095
Of course it's clear. I'm right here.

401
00:32:18,904 --> 00:32:20,339
Check, one, two, three.

402
00:32:22,602 --> 00:32:27,414
1, 2, 3, 4. Jump...

403
00:32:27,414 --> 00:32:30,842
Stomp... Stomp again. Turn around.

404
00:32:32,446 --> 00:32:37,647
Stomp... Bye-bye...

405
00:32:38,188 --> 00:32:39,792
This is for self-defense.

406
00:32:40,163 --> 00:32:44,300
It's easy to use. Just aim it at them
and press the button.

407
00:32:45,668 --> 00:32:47,373
Don't use it unless you have to.

408
00:32:47,880 --> 00:32:48,708
Mm.

409
00:32:50,666 --> 00:32:52,102
You scared me.

410
00:32:54,027 --> 00:32:56,745
- Looks like we're ready.
- Ouch.

411
00:32:58,907 --> 00:33:01,997
I'm ready. You're the one who isn't.

412
00:33:03,855 --> 00:33:06,067
You're going undercover as a host

413
00:33:06,082 --> 00:33:07,795
when you don't even know how?

414
00:33:08,954 --> 00:33:11,588
The first and most important rule.

415
00:33:11,592 --> 00:33:13,390
Don't be stressed.

416
00:33:13,390 --> 00:33:15,793
And don't upset the customers.

417
00:33:16,097 --> 00:33:16,992
That's it?

418
00:33:18,174 --> 00:33:20,538
You can really control that?

419
00:33:20,538 --> 00:33:23,341
Of course. You just have to smile.

420
00:33:23,341 --> 00:33:26,229
However you do it,
make them stay focused on you.

421
00:33:27,968 --> 00:33:28,947
Smile.

422
00:33:30,366 --> 00:33:32,274
Come on, hurry.
Don't make that blank look.

423
00:33:32,274 --> 00:33:34,570
Don't make that blank look.
Think of it like the real thing.

424
00:33:34,570 --> 00:33:36,462
- Smile.
- Mm.

425
00:33:36,462 --> 00:33:37,644
Okay.

426
00:33:39,231 --> 00:33:41,764
Yeah, that's good.

427
00:33:41,764 --> 00:33:44,348
Woo.

428
00:33:44,348 --> 00:33:48,063
Captain! Smile!

429
00:33:48,535 --> 00:33:50,698
Don't look blank. Captain.

430
00:33:51,186 --> 00:33:52,858
Okay, ready?

431
00:33:56,810 --> 00:34:00,676
5, 6, 7, 8. Jump...

432
00:34:00,676 --> 00:34:08,309
Chest... Step... Turn around...

433
00:34:08,309 --> 00:34:13,510
Stomp... Bye-bye...

434
00:34:13,510 --> 00:34:16,127
Bye-bye!

435
00:34:45,746 --> 00:34:46,528
Hey.

436
00:34:46,528 --> 00:34:47,296
Argh.

437
00:34:55,438 --> 00:34:57,296
- Hey, boy.
- Yes.

438
00:34:57,296 --> 00:35:01,686
- What's your name, sweetie?
- Uh... Biscuit.

439
00:35:01,855 --> 00:35:06,600
Biscuit? That sounds delicious.

440
00:35:07,478 --> 00:35:11,565
Smile... Remember rule number two?

441
00:35:14,908 --> 00:35:17,070
Do you remember rule number two?

442
00:35:19,552 --> 00:35:23,047
Rule number two.
When you're with a customer,

443
00:35:23,402 --> 00:35:25,259
ask questions.

444
00:35:26,137 --> 00:35:27,032
Hello.

445
00:35:27,623 --> 00:35:28,670
(What's your name?)

446
00:35:28,974 --> 00:35:30,595
And what should I call you?

447
00:35:30,916 --> 00:35:34,023
- I'm Tukta.
- Oh, Tukta.

448
00:35:34,293 --> 00:35:36,033
What kind of vibe do you want today?

449
00:35:36,489 --> 00:35:39,174
So, Tukta, what kind of vibe
are you after tonight?

450
00:35:39,309 --> 00:35:42,652
Something warm and gentle.

451
00:35:42,663 --> 00:35:44,798
But with a little spice too.

452
00:35:44,798 --> 00:35:46,924
Hehe, sure.

453
00:35:47,110 --> 00:35:48,393
What would you like to drink tonight?

454
00:35:49,896 --> 00:35:51,838
So, would you like something to drink?

455
00:35:52,294 --> 00:35:55,790
Um, sparkling wine
sounds best right now, dear.

456
00:35:56,955 --> 00:35:59,234
- Sure.
- Good. Nice.

457
00:35:59,555 --> 00:36:01,075
Every line was spot-on.

458
00:36:01,075 --> 00:36:02,595
And don't forget, Captain.

459
00:36:03,017 --> 00:36:05,685
Entertain the guests.
Tease them to their heart's content.

460
00:36:07,981 --> 00:36:09,130
So...

461
00:36:10,565 --> 00:36:13,436
Let me go get the drinks.

462
00:36:14,314 --> 00:36:16,644
- Okay.
- Sparkling wine, right?

463
00:36:18,822 --> 00:36:19,819
Nicely done.

464
00:36:20,089 --> 00:36:23,973
But were you maybe getting a little
too close? Take it easy. Read the room.

465
00:36:23,973 --> 00:36:27,198
I was just doing what the teacher
taught me. What did I do wrong?

466
00:36:27,992 --> 00:36:30,541
Heh. Just wait till the night's over.

467
00:36:54,283 --> 00:36:57,188
- Did you just hit a guest?
- Uh.

468
00:36:58,707 --> 00:37:00,649
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to.

469
00:37:00,649 --> 00:37:03,149
Didn't mean? Your foot
nearly smacked me in the face.

470
00:37:03,149 --> 00:37:05,935
I-I'm ticklish.

471
00:37:07,353 --> 00:37:09,059
I'm telling Por.

472
00:37:09,481 --> 00:37:11,659
Yeah, I'm sorry.

473
00:37:11,912 --> 00:37:13,956
Can I apologize for my friend?

474
00:37:14,462 --> 00:37:18,515
Then let me make it up to you for him.

475
00:37:18,903 --> 00:37:20,305
And how exactly
are you going to do that?

476
00:37:22,551 --> 00:37:24,864
Well, just now,

477
00:37:25,101 --> 00:37:28,815
what part of my friend
were you trying to touch?

478
00:37:30,876 --> 00:37:33,645
You can touch me instead.

479
00:37:34,219 --> 00:37:36,853
You want to touch here?

480
00:37:38,441 --> 00:37:39,538
Or here?

481
00:37:41,328 --> 00:37:43,017
Or maybe like this?

482
00:37:44,081 --> 00:37:46,056
This is just the appetizer.

483
00:37:47,306 --> 00:37:49,923
Then how about we skip
to the main course?

484
00:37:50,025 --> 00:37:52,422
Sure. This way, please.

485
00:37:59,852 --> 00:38:05,036
Wait here for a second, okay?

486
00:38:56,759 --> 00:39:00,406
Ow! Biscuit, make the drink.

487
00:39:01,369 --> 00:39:02,517
It's okay.

488
00:39:10,977 --> 00:39:13,847
Record everything. Wait for my signal.

489
00:39:16,480 --> 00:39:17,920
(Biscuit)

490
00:39:18,407 --> 00:39:19,487
Roger that.

491
00:39:21,767 --> 00:39:23,979
Signal's clear, Captain.

492
00:40:18,927 --> 00:40:22,287
Finish your drink,

493
00:40:22,287 --> 00:40:23,993
and I'll let you touch me once.

494
00:40:25,512 --> 00:40:27,657
Don't tempt me.

495
00:40:30,308 --> 00:40:31,355
Oh.

496
00:40:33,179 --> 00:40:34,766
I'm ready for more.

497
00:40:36,927 --> 00:40:41,301
But if you do two glasses for me,

498
00:40:42,905 --> 00:40:45,354
I might have a special reward for you.

499
00:40:46,417 --> 00:40:48,849
You can move closer and touch me here.

500
00:40:54,084 --> 00:40:58,559
Whoa, then make it four.

501
00:40:58,559 --> 00:41:02,223
Maybe I'll find us somewhere private,

502
00:41:02,223 --> 00:41:04,975
and let you touch me wherever you want.

503
00:41:05,718 --> 00:41:08,471
No matter how many glasses,
I'll take them all on.

504
00:41:13,064 --> 00:41:15,445
- Haha.
- Nicely done.

505
00:41:19,480 --> 00:41:20,781
Lie down here for now.

506
00:41:20,798 --> 00:41:23,043
- I'll get you some water.
- Yeah.

507
00:41:24,074 --> 00:41:26,725
Krit, over here. I can lose
the customer now.

508
00:41:27,113 --> 00:41:28,194
Be careful.

509
00:41:29,089 --> 00:41:31,993
Nothing suspicious
in the back area so far.

510
00:41:36,256 --> 00:41:38,934
(Wayu)

511
00:41:38,934 --> 00:41:41,096
Hey, Wayu.

512
00:41:42,588 --> 00:41:43,896
We met at Moonlit.

513
00:41:44,472 --> 00:41:45,198
Yeah?

514
00:41:46,262 --> 00:41:48,575
- It's me.
- Oh, Mr. Ice.

515
00:41:48,896 --> 00:41:50,467
Wow, you remember me?

516
00:41:50,467 --> 00:41:53,169
Of course I do. With your name
and that body, how could I forget?

517
00:41:53,743 --> 00:41:55,077
Didn't expect to run into you here.

518
00:41:55,549 --> 00:42:00,209
- Yeah.
- About that makeup time you promised.

519
00:42:00,209 --> 00:42:03,604
Can I cash that in here?
I'm feeling lonely.

520
00:42:04,347 --> 00:42:07,184
Sure, we can do that.

521
